# .mdc File Structure & Best Practices

## File Naming Convention
- Format: `NNN-descriptive-name.mdc` (NNN = 001-299)
- 001-099: Core/workspace rules
- 100-199: Integration rules  
- 200-299: Pattern/feature-specific rules
- Higher numbers take precedence if rules conflict

## MDC File Components

### 1. Frontmatter (YAML)
```yaml
---
description: Brief purpose summary (appears in AI context)
globs: comma,separated,glob,patterns
alwaysApply: true|false
---
```

### 2. Body Content
- Keep under 25 lines for optimal token efficiency
- Use concise/shorthand notation
- Tag files with @ for cross-references
- Focus on key directives and constraints

## Rule Types

| Type | Description | Frontmatter Settings |
|------|-------------|---------------------|
| **Always** | Always included in model context | `alwaysApply: true`, `globs:` optional |
| **Auto Attached** | Included when files match glob pattern | `alwaysApply: false`, `globs: pattern` |
| **Agent Requested** | AI decides when to include based on description | `description: detailed`, `globs:` blank |
| **Manual** | Only when explicitly referenced with @ruleName | minimal frontmatter |

## Best Practices
- Use @ tags for file references: `@buildAIConfig.ts`
- Keep rules focused and actionable
- Avoid redundancy across rule files
- Test rule effectiveness with relevant file patterns
- Update via Cursor UI, not direct file edits

